<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id746a56f3-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s22302"><num value="22302">§ 22302.</num><heading> Purposes</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The purposes of the corporation are—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id746a56f4-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s22302/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to serve as a coordinating, research, and educational agency and clearinghouse for symphony orchestras to help strengthen the work in their local communities;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id746a56f5-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s22302/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to assist in the formation of new symphony orchestras;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id746a56f6-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s22302/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> to encourage and recognize the work of America’s musicians, conductors, and composers, through suitable means; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id746a56f7-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s22302/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> to aid the expansion of the musical and cultural life of the United States through suitable educational and service activities.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id746a56f8-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1302">112 Stat. 1302</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
